Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,_,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.21,0:00:03.19,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Sleigh Beggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.21,0:00:09.43,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Dear child, with the name \Nof a neighbor of long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.52,0:00:23.18,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,A being nearer to us than the humans, \Nbearing a burden too great for a human child.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.07,0:00:32.17,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,How adorable you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:44.35,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,What will you find at the end of \Nyour journey with the failure born
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.85,0:00:48.11,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,in the shadows of the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:08.10,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you find.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.54,0:02:53.27,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Those are wooly bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.73,0:02:54.97,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.64,0:03:00.02,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,They consume the cold in the air and \Ngrow fleece on their bodies, like sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.50,0:03:02.97,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,That means they multiply during the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.43,0:03:08.72,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot this year, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.07,0:03:11.09,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are they neighbors?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.95,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,No, they're closer to animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:17.45,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Although very few humans can see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:29.20,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.50,0:03:30.31,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:42.55,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:43.62,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You're good at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:51.00,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Their wool is perfect for using \Nin magic and sorcery tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.63,0:03:53.83,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Angelica asks me to do this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:55.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.37,0:03:58.75,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You can use the leftovers to \Nmake a pillow or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:00.71,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You'll probably sleep well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:06.14,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You might get to have the \Ndreams you want to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:09.29,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The dreams I want to have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.58,0:04:12.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take a little when we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.76,0:04:14.60,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.93,0:04:18.41,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't trim from their \Nlimbs. Just the torso.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.41,0:04:20.90,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. You could have told me sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:44.37,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a haul.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:46.70,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.70,0:04:48.22,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You keep practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:53.91,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:54.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:59.56,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,If you find one that seems a bit \Ndifferent, tell me before you touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.59,0:05:01.56,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.34,0:05:17.77,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to talk to him \Nas soon as I got home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.28,0:05:22.05,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know when I should bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:27.46,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's that I don't know {\i0}what {\i1}to tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.90,0:05:30.24,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.86,0:05:32.10,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.75,0:05:36.81,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.81,0:05:37.83,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He's so strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.49,0:05:46.54,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Has it always been so hard to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.34,0:05:57.48,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's different from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.63,0:06:00.00,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:03.75,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:05.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.35,0:06:06.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's so cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.70,0:06:10.25,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias said to get him before I touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.47,0:06:12.13,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What happens if I touch it first?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.09,0:06:13.88,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:20.52,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot, it didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:22.06,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.57,0:06:31.74,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Fire doesn't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.40,0:06:48.39,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.31,0:06:57.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.29,0:07:11.29,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You're done breeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:12.61,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to the fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.07,0:07:20.95,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:23.40,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Elias, what was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.40,0:07:27.84,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,A snow bug. Unlike wooly \Nbugs, they eat warmth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.09,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,It took her heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.09,0:07:31.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.94,0:07:33.73,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Chise didn't touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:35.59,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,It charged at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.90,0:07:37.05,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:40.59,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been hungry, since\N summer is their breeding season.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:44.11,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,We need to warm her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.11,0:07:46.82,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Eli... as...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.59,0:08:04.70,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.03,0:08:07.91,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm quite a bit warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.63,0:08:11.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:13.21,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Ruth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:15.05,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,He went to check on the snow bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:19.98,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.98,0:08:21.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:24.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.84,0:08:28.28,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,It was cold when you were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.62,0:08:31.20,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,But it's warm with you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.25,0:08:33.38,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.09,0:08:37.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.41,0:08:38.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:50.12,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Chise...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:52.16,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:56.01,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, how was the land of dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.35,0:08:59.28,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, it was... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:00.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:02.75,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:08.59,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There was a huge snake-like dragon \Nin the river, dancing elves,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.16,0:09:10.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,and flowers that bloom with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:13.44,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.72,0:09:19.16,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-san told me a lot, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:21.32,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So did Nevin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.23,0:09:23.33,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Nevin?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:27.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,They both gave me a lot of encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.46,0:09:33.83,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias, did I look tasty?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:38.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.21,0:09:40.26,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You were awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.67,0:09:44.25,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was a dream until \NLindel-san told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.49,0:09:46.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But I was just curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:52.18,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.82,0:09:56.42,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Eli—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.42,0:10:00.83,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, that's a memory that you don't need.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.83,0:10:01.73,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.88,0:10:32.89,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:36.30,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's about someone important to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:42.00,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I do need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.46,0:10:47.79,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impulse is a scary thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:54.88,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You're really not scared of me, Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.83,0:11:05.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to think I'm really afraid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.08,0:11:11.59,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Am I not scary to a human?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:24.09,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I used to have family.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.91,0:11:28.91,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A mom, a dad, and a younger\Nbrother who was still very little.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.42,0:11:33.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mom and Dad both had the sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.41,0:11:36.97,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,They were really close to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.21,0:11:43.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I was always terrified of the scary \Nthings that swarmed toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.02,0:11:49.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But I was always safe with my dad around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:51.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.70,0:11:56.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,my dad vanished with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.20,0:12:02.48,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think my mom was tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:05.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.48,0:12:10.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,She left me and passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.75,0:12:16.20,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I loved my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:20.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,but they didn't take me with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.39,0:12:25.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So, I didn't want a family anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.26,0:12:27.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.19,0:12:34.97,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, you called me family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.97,0:12:43.51,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The future he spoke of always involved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.12,0:12:48.95,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So I let myself think that \Nwe had a future together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.44,0:12:54.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to learn about my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:12:58.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,but you wouldn't tell me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.81,0:13:06.08,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So when Lindel-san told me about your past,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.41,0:13:08.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.48,0:13:10.60,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.60,0:13:14.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's not you that I'm afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:17.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's you letting go of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:21.54,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Humans lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.92,0:13:25.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't deny that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:27.40,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.88,0:13:30.57,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.92,0:13:33.79,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,You're my apprentice, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.51,0:13:39.58,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Chise,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:45.30,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,how does one feel when \Nthey care for another?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:46.89,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,How can you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.83,0:13:48.92,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:53.29,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,As I've said before, I can't empathize.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:58.11,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,So even if I wanted to say to you what \Nyou said to me, I would be lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:02.46,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.82,0:14:07.42,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I was terribly cold when you were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:13.75,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,What would you call that, in your words?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.38,0:14:23.17,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Loneliness, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:31.07,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.94,0:14:34.57,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I was {\i1}lonely{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:40.30,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He really is just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:43.31,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A child that ended up in an adult's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.30,0:14:47.77,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I bought you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.33,0:14:50.61,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:57.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess I'm your teacher \Nwhen it comes to human things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.41,0:15:00.78,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.43,0:15:04.25,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to learning from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:07.02,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,teacher of human things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:12.19,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise, teacher of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.82,0:15:17.39,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, I hadn't gotten \Na good look at your wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:19.02,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Can you show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:21.59,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.76,0:15:27.73,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same color as your hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.16,0:15:31.04,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Though I was planning on finishing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.40,0:15:34.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone else supposed \Nto do the finishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.77,0:15:39.78,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,We also use our wands to help\Nus along on our long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.05,0:15:48.06,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,The seniors bless the wands of the youth\Nso that they can continue their journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:55.58,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Then if there ever comes a time to \Nmake a second one, I'll ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.40,0:15:57.92,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:15:59.78,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.97,0:16:01.47,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.47,0:16:03.65,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll study magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.17,0:16:05.14,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.66,0:16:10.39,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He still won't talk to me about himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.48,0:16:16.44,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything new while I was gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:20.18,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. Maybe a few birds that came to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.18,0:16:22.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Migratory birds or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.67,0:16:24.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I would have liked to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:35.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is from back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:41.97,Default,Doggo,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.97,0:16:43.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.16,0:16:47.95,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I should get to studying first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.94,0:18:33.99,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.08,0:18:37.98,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.98,0:18:40.13,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have the usual medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.35,0:18:41.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Simon-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.26,0:18:43.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:56.73,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's elderberry syrup.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.56,0:18:58.67,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.23,0:19:01.32,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's good for your throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.92,0:19:08.89,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.52,0:19:14.86,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,I just remembered, this is the first \Nthing Ainsworth gave me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.70,0:19:17.01,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.30,0:19:21.93,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,I'm technically his supervisor, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:24.49,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,I even used to act the part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.96,0:19:27.44,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, with this thing \Nbeing the way it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:34.52,Magus-Flashback,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.19,0:19:43.94,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,He's kind, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:46.46,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:47.96,Default,Priest,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:10.80,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A guest? This late?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.66,0:20:12.89,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.10,0:20:17.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:22.65,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Is the master of the house available?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:24.90,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Ashen Eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:30.42,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,I'd heard a rumor that \Na new mage was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:33.45,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,I came to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.87,0:20:36.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This man's been alive for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.57,0:20:38.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He comes occasionally to chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:41.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful. He isn't human.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:45.28,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,You have no reason to be fearful of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.28,0:20:48.63,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,I don't intend to harm you one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:58.65,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,You carry the blood of the Far East.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.05,0:21:01.07,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He smells of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.50,0:21:04.45,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,But this hair, those eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.21,0:21:10.22,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Yours aren't quite the same as those of \Nthe inhabitants of that island nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.70,0:21:16.74,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,I believe your lineage may also carry\Na tinge of blood from the western continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.54,0:21:22.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I don't know much about my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.14,0:21:23.66,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:27.80,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Bonds of blood are insignificant \Nin living as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:31.72,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Humans overthink everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.96,0:21:36.28,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,You ought to drown yourselves \Nin your true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.05,0:21:38.76,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.13,0:21:47.02,Default,Megagramps,0000,0000,0000,,A gift for the youngest born of those \Nwho capture and bind my people!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.10,0:21:49.78,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Ashen Eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.47,0:22:15.33,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Chise...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.83,0:24:01.92,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Guided by instinct, are we brought to \Na rift between humans and non-humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.92,0:24:04.29,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,one which we can never overcome?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.72,0:24:06.82,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.82,0:24:09.37,Default,Bonehead,0000,0000,0000,,And selfish, too.
